body.description: Redefine everyday file transfers with the Samsung FIT Plus USB 3.1 Flash Drive. Just plug it in and expand the storage of your devices with an unnoticeable, seamless fit. Designed with a key ring to prevent loss. Fast and convenient read speeds up to 400MB/s*, so that you have more time to work, play, watch, and create. A reliable and secure solution for your personal photos, videos, music, documents, and files. Safeguard your data backed by a 5-year limited warranty (water proof, shock proof, magnet proof, temperature proof, x-ray proof). Experience Samsung's industry-leading V-NAND (64 layer) technology. *Up to 400MB/s for 256/128GB models; Up to 300MB/s for 64GB model and up to 200MB/s for 32GB model. Actual speeds may vary by host device and/or usage conditions. **Minimum of 10 secs for 256/128GB models; Minimum of 14 secs for 64/32GB models. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Lifesaver for Both Me and My Feline Friend: Samsung FIT Plus USB Flash Drive
reviews.reviewText: I can't emphasize enough just how much the Samsung FIT Plus USB Flash Drive has been a game-changer in my life. It's not an exaggeration to say that this little device saved both me and my beloved cat from a major disaster.Let's start with the compact design and convenience. The Samsung FIT Plus is incredibly small, yet mighty in its capabilities. Its sleek form allows it to stay plugged into my laptop without protruding or getting in the way. No more worrying about losing or misplacing a bulky flash drive. It's always there, ready to spring into action when I need it.But it's not just the size that makes this flash drive remarkable; it's the lightning-fast speed and ample storage capacity. With read speeds of up to 400MB/s, transferring large files or backing up important documents has become a breeze. I no longer have to endure the excruciatingly slow transfer times of my previous flash drives.Speaking of storage, the Samsung FIT Plus provides a generous 128GB of space, ensuring I have ample room for all my files, photos, and videos. It's like having a portable vault that can hold an entire digital world.Now, here's where the story takes a twist. One fateful day, my mischievous cat managed to knock over a glass of water directly onto my laptop. Panic ensued as I rushed to save both my precious data and my furry companion's life. With lightning speed, I unplugged the Samsung FIT Plus from my laptop, knowing that my files were safely stored within its waterproof and shockproof design.Miraculously, the flash drive emerged unscathed, and so did my data. Thanks to the durability and reliability of the Samsung FIT Plus, my important files remained intact, allowing me to continue my work without missing a beat. It truly was a lifesaver in that moment of crisis.But the Samsung FIT Plus didn't stop there. Its compatibility with a wide range of devices, including smartphones and tablets, meant that I could easily expand their storage capacity as well. No more worrying about running out of space for photos or videos during trips or important events. This little powerhouse ensured that I never missed capturing a single moment.In conclusion, the Samsung FIT Plus USB Flash Drive is an absolute gem. Its compact size, lightning-fast speed, generous storage capacity, and exceptional durability make it a must-have device for anyone in need of seamless data management. Whether you're a student, professional, or a digital enthusiast like me, this flash drive is a reliable companion that can save the day in unexpected situations. Trust me, it saved my life and my cat's, and it will undoubtedly become an invaluable asset in yours too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The Performance and Reliability you expected from Samsung - GREAT value!!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the SAMSUNG FIT Plus 3.1 USB Flash Drive with 128GB capacity, and I can confidently say that I am impressed. This compact yet powerful flash drive provides instant, seamless and unobtrusive storage that is perfect for laptops, tablets, TVs, car audio systems, gaming consoles, and more.One of the key features of this flash drive is its ability to be left in your devices without any risks of accidental bumps or removal. As someone who's always on the go, this feature is invaluable because it gives me the assurance that my files and documents are always within reach, without any worries of losing them.Another noteworthy feature is its fast transfer speed of up to 400MB/s using the latest USB 3.1 standard. I can transfer a 3GB 4K UHD video file from my FIT Plus to my PC in just 10 seconds. This feature saves me time and effort, especially when working with larger files.In addition to its impressive performance, the FIT Plus is also a tough and reliable flash drive. Its waterproof, shock-proof, temperature-proof, magnet-proof, and X-ray-proof body ensures that my files remain secure wherever I take them. The brand's leadership in flash memory also gives me the peace of mind that my valuable data is always in good hands.Finally, as someone who values quality, I appreciate that all firmware and components, including Samsung's world-renowned DRAM and NAND, are produced in-house. This gives me the assurance that I'm getting a reliable and high-quality product.In conclusion, the SAMSUNG FIT Plus 3.1 USB Flash Drive is an excellent choice for anyone who needs extra storage for their devices. Its seamless and unobtrusive design, fast transfer speed, reliability, and durability make it a standout product that I strongly recommend. If you're in the market for a reliable and trustworthy flash drive, the SAMSUNG FIT Plus is definitely worth considering.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good performance second only to BAR Plus
reviews.reviewText: I'm surprised by its performance, tested using agnostics, is almost the same as BAR Plus but with a shorter form factor. However, it's wider than BAR Plus which makes BAR Plus better for my uses as I have port layout that's too close to each other . So if you prefer a small form factor, high performance and reasonable cost USB Flash drive, FIT Plus is what I recommend. In my case because of the port layout, I'll stick with BAR Plus. Yes there are higher performance USB Flash drive but at more than twice the cost. Samsung FIT Plus and BAR Plus are the best value for the money as of Jan 2024.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Low Price, Small Size & Fast Performance
reviews.reviewText: Excellent USB flash drive. Formatted to NTFS with 238GB available. Write speed for a 1GB file on a SuperSpeed USB 3.1 port was 105 MB/s and transfer was steady. Write speed for a 2GB file was around 65 MB/s and the speed fluctuated. These are excellent speeds for a tiny flash drive. The build quality feels premium and will not crack like my Sandisk Fit did shortly after purchase. No complaints other than I wish it was available in a 512GB capacity. For a sale price of $20 you can not beat this. If you need insane speed, I also have the Samsung Shield T7 and it transfers at more than 1000MB/s!
Love this drive! small, large capacity and fast transfers!

reviews.reviewTitle: Good all round drive that's very compact
reviews.reviewText: Bought this and Samsung's blue "USB Type C" drive at the same time. They both tested nearly identically (very good sequential reads, ok sequential writes, and decent random writes). These make good storage drives, but what's especially unique is the random write performance which will allow you to run an OS decently enough on them compared to most USB drives.If I had known they performed identically I would have gotten more of these Fit Plus instead of those blue Type C ones since these are much more compact. Unless you need the USB C interface, get these instead
Produto de alto padrão! Pequeno, compacto e extremamente rápido. Recomendo!
Ótimo custo/beneficio excelente e melhor marca.
It has a high speed and it's small. It has just a little less than the 128 GB, but it's normal. Just it's tight at the moment of taking it off from the computer
